{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01R9B5ZLwaA81q4buXwXBtpB","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me compile my findings into a detailed report.\n\n## Comprehensive Cloche Project Analysis\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the Cloche grow-coding system. Here's my detailed analysis covering all aspects you requested:\n\n---\n\n### 1. CLI COMMAND STRUCTURE (cmd/cloche/main.go)\n\n**Architecture Pattern:**\n- Cloche uses a **two-tier command handling system**:\n  1. **Commands without daemon connection** (lines 41-77): init, health, get, set, tasks\n  2. **Daemon-requiring commands** (lines 79-129): run, status, logs, poll, list, stop, delete, loop, shutdown\n\n**How Subcommands Are Registered:**\nEach subcommand is dispatched via a `switch` statement on `os.Args[1]`, then help is handled before execution:\n\n```go\nswitch os.Args[1] {\ncase \"init\":\n    if hasHelpFlag(os.Args[2:]) {\n        printSubcommandHelp(\"init\")\n        return\n    }\n    cmdInit(os.Args[2:])\n    return\ncase \"run\":\n    // ... connect to daemon first\n    cmdRun(ctx, client, os.Args[2:])\n}\n```\n\n**Help System:**\n- Help text is centralized in `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go` in the `subcommandHelp` map (lines 10-305)\n- Each subcommand entry includes usage, flags, examples, and detailed descriptions formatted for LLM consumption\n- Help is triggered via `--help`, `-h`, or `help <command>`\n\n**Subcommand Categories:**\n| Category | Commands | Notes |\n|----------|----------|-------|\n| Project Setup | init, health | No daemon needed |\n| Workflow Runs | run, status, logs, poll, list, stop, delete | Daemon-based gRPC calls |\n| Orchestration | tasks, loop | Uses gRPC or HTTP API |\n| Context | get, set | Run-specific state management |\n| Daemon Mgmt | shutdown | Direct gRPC |\n\n---\n\n### 2. WORKFLOW DSL TYPES (internal/domain/workflow.go)\n\n**Core Data Model:**\n\n```go\ntype Workflow struct {\n    Name      string                    // e.g. \"develop\"\n    Location  WorkflowLocation          // \"container\" or \"host\"\n    Steps     map[string]*Step          // Named steps\n    Wiring    []Wire                    // step:result -> step mappings\n    Collects  []Collect                 // Multi-result aggregation (fanout join)\n    EntryStep string                    // First step to execute\n    Config    map[string]string         // Workflow-level config (container.image, host.agent_command)\n}\n\ntype Step struct {\n    Name    string                      // Unique within workflow\n    Type    StepType                    // agent | script | workflow\n    Results []string                    // Declared possible outcomes\n    Config  map[string]string           // Step-specific config (prompt, run, workflow_name, etc)\n}\n\ntype Wire struct {\n    From      string                    // Source step\n    Result    string                    // Which result triggers this wire\n    To        string                    // Target step (\"done\" or \"abort\" for terminals)\n    OutputMap []OutputMapping           // Optional env var injection\n}\n\ntype OutputMapping struct {\n    EnvVar string                       // Env var to set (e.g. \"TASK_ID\")\n    Path   OutputPath                   // JSON path expression (e.g. output.id)\n}\n\ntype OutputPath struct {\n    Segments []PathSegment              // Navigates JSON: field access or array indexing\n}\n```\n\n**Step Type Inference (parser.go:224-253):**\nThe parser infers step type from the presence of fields:\n- `prompt` → `StepTypeAgent`\n- `run` → `StepTypeScript`\n- `workflow_name` → `StepTypeWorkflow` (host-only)\n\nA step **must have exactly one** of these three. Having zero or multiple is a parse error.\n\n**Results and Wiring:**\n- Each step declares its possible results (e.g., `results = [success, fail, retry]`)\n- Wiring connects results to next steps: `step_a:success -> step_b`\n- **Every declared result must be wired** (validation enforces this at parse time)\n- **All steps must be reachable** from the entry step\n- **Fanout** supported: multiple wires from the same (step, result) pair\n- **Collect mode** supports awaiting multiple step results before proceeding\n\n**Location-Based Validation:**\n```go\nfunc (w *Workflow) ValidateLocation() error {\n    if w.Location == LocationContainer {\n        // workflow_name steps forbidden in container workflows\n    }\n}\n```\n\nOnly host workflows (host.cloche) can dispatch container workflow runs via `workflow_name` steps.\n\n---\n\n### 3. WORKFLOW PARSING & LOADING\n\n**Parser Design (internal/dsl/parser.go):**\n\n```go\n// Single workflow parsing\nfunc Parse(input string, opts ...ParseOption) (*domain.Workflow, error)\nfunc ParseForContainer(input string) (*domain.Workflow, error)\nfunc ParseForHost(input string) (*domain.Workflow, error)\n\n// Multiple workflows in host.cloche\nfunc ParseAllForHost(input string) (map[string]*domain.Workflow, error)\n```\n\n**Lexer + Recursive Descent Parser:**\n- Lexer tokenizes input (tokens defined in `/workspace/internal/dsl/token.go`)\n- Tokens: `TokenIdent`, `TokenString`, `TokenLBrace`, `TokenRBrace`, `TokenArrow` (`->`), `TokenColon`, `TokenDot`, `TokenEquals`, `TokenLBracket`, `TokenRBracket`, `TokenComma`, `TokenInt`\n- Parser uses lookahead (current + peek tokens) for recursive descent\n- Comments and whitespace skipped by lexer\n\n**Parsing Phases:**\n\n1. **Workflow header** (line 99): `workflow \"<name>\" { ... }`\n2. **Config blocks** (line 164): `container { image = \"...\" }` or `host { agent_command = \"...\" }`\n3. **Steps** (line 197): `step <name> { ... }` with fields parsed recursively\n4. **Wiring** (line 402): `step_a:result -> step_b [ENVVAR = output.path, ...]`\n5. **Collect** (line 513): `collect all(step1:result, step2:result) -> target`\n\n**Output Path Parsing (line 478):**\nNavigates JSON structure: `output`, `output.field`, `output[0]`, `output.a.b.c`, `output.items[0].name`\n\n**Validation Sequence:**\n- Parse-time checks for duplicate workflows, missing names\n- `Workflow.ValidateLocation()` (line 233): ensures workflow_name only in host workflows\n- `Workflow.Validate()` (line 145): full DAG validation\n- `Workflow.ValidateConfig()` (line 261): warns about unrecognized config keys\n\n---\n\n### 4. EXISTING SUBCOMMAND IMPLEMENTATIONS\n\n**Pattern across all subcommands:**\n\n```go\nfunc cmd<Name>(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n    // 1. Parse flags/arguments\n    var workflow, prompt string\n    for i := 0; i < len(args); i++ {\n        switch args[i] {\n        case \"--workflow\":\n            workflow = args[i+1]\n            i++\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // 2. Validate required arguments\n    if workflow == \"\" {\n        fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: ...\\n\")\n        os.Exit(1)\n    }\n    \n    // 3. Call daemon via gRPC\n    resp, err := client.RunWorkflow(ctx, &pb.RunWorkflowRequest{...})\n    if err != nil {\n        fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n        os.Exit(1)\n    }\n    \n    // 4. Format and output result\n    fmt.Printf(\"Started run: %s\\n\", resp.RunId)\n}\n```\n\n**Key Implementations:**\n\n**cmdRun** (main.go:133-193):\n- Resolves workflow image from `.cloche/<name>.cloche` (dsl.ParseForContainer)\n- Sends RunWorkflowRequest to daemon\n- Prints run ID\n\n**cmdStatus** (main.go:195-232):\n- Queries GetStatus RPC\n- Formats tabular output with run state, steps, timestamps, error\n\n**cmdLogs** (main.go:290-375):\n- Handles `--step <name>`, `--type <full|script|llm>`, `--follow` flags\n- Uses gRPC metadata header for follow mode\n- Streams log entries, parses Claude Code streams\n\n**cmdPoll** (poll.go:12-77):\n- Polls GetStatus every 2 seconds\n- Tracks step count and state changes\n- Exits with status code 0 (succeeded) or 1 (failed/cancelled)\n- Detects container death after 1-minute threshold\n\n**cmdList** (main.go:234-288):\n- Optional `--all` flag to list all projects\n- Default filters to current project directory\n- Formats tabular output with truncated titles/errors\n\n**Non-daemon Commands:**\n\n**cmdInit** (init.go:138-232):\n- Creates `.cloche/` directory structure\n- Writes workflow templates, Dockerfile, prompt files\n- Updates .gitignore for run directories\n- Flags: `--workflow`, `--base-image`\n\n**cmdGet/cmdSet** (main.go:563-613):\n- Resolve run context from env vars: CLOCHE_RUN_ID, CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR\n- Read/write from run's context.json file\n- Set supports reading from stdin with `-` value\n\n**cmdHealth** (health.go:24-92):\n- Calls HTTP endpoint `/api/projects`\n- Formats project health with pass/fail counts\n- Color codes status (green/yellow/red) for TTY\n\n**cmdTasks** (main.go:450-534):\n- Calls HTTP endpoint `/api/projects/{projectDir}/tasks`\n- Parses JSON task list\n- Formats table with ID, status, assignment, run, title\n\n---\n\n### 5. PORTS/INTERFACES (internal/ports/)\n\n**RunStore Interface** (store.go:10-19):\n```go\ntype RunStore interface {\n    CreateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\n    GetRun(ctx context.Context, id string) (*domain.Run, error)\n    UpdateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\n    DeleteRun(ctx context.Context, id string) error\n    ListRuns(ctx context.Context, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListProjects(ctx context.Context) ([]string, error)\n    ListChildRuns(ctx context.Context, parentRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n}\n```\n\n**CaptureStore Interface** (store.go:21-24):\nPersists step execution logs and metadata (StepExecution records).\n\n**LogStore Interface** (store.go:36-41):\nManages log files by type (full, script, llm), indexed by run and step.\n\n**ContainerRuntime Interface** (container.go:24-33):\n```go\ntype ContainerRuntime interface {\n    Start(ctx context.Context, cfg ContainerConfig) (containerID string, err error)\n    Stop(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n    AttachOutput(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n    Wait(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (exitCode int, err error)\n    CopyFrom(ctx context.Context, containerID string, srcPath, dstPath string) error\n    Logs(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (string, error)\n    Remove(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n    Inspect(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (*ContainerStatus, error)\n}\n```\n\n**AgentAdapter Interface** (agent.go:10-12):\n```go\ntype AgentAdapter interface {\n    Name() string\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (result string, err error)\n}\n```\nAbstraction for any coding agent (Claude Code, Codex, etc).\n\n**EvolutionStore Interface** (store.go:54-58):\nTracks workflow mutations and self-evolution history.\n\n---\n\n### 6. WORKFLOW DSL SYNTAX (docs/workflows.md)\n\n**Complete Grammar:**\n\n```\nworkflow \"<name>\" {\n  [ <config-block> ]\n  [ <step-definitions> ]\n  [ <wiring> ]\n  [ <collect> ]\n}\n\n<config-block> ::= \"container\" | \"host\" \"{\" <key-value-pairs> \"}\"\n<key-value-pairs> ::= <ident> \"=\" <value> [ \",\" <key-value-pairs> ]\n\n<step-definitions> ::= \"step\" <ident> \"{\" <fields> \"}\"\n<fields> ::= <key> \"=\" <value> [ <fields> ]\n           | \"results\" \"=\" \"[\" <ident-list> \"]\" [ <fields> ]\n           | <key> \"{\" <fields> \"}\" [ <fields> ]\n\n<wiring> ::= <ident> \":\" <ident> \"->\" <ident> [ \"[\" <output-mappings> \"]\" ]\n<output-mappings> ::= <ident> \"=\" <path> [ \",\" <output-mappings> ]\n<path> ::= \"output\" [ \".\" <ident> ]* [ \"[\" <int> \"]\" ]*\n\n<collect> ::= \"collect\" (\"all\" | \"any\") \"(\" <conditions> \")\" \"->\" <ident>\n<conditions> ::= <ident> \":\" <ident> [ \",\" <conditions> ]\n```\n\n**Step Type Inference:**\n- `prompt` field → Agent step\n- `run` field → Script step\n- `workflow_name` field → Workflow dispatch (host-only)\n- Exactly one required\n\n**Config Keys:**\n- **Container workflows**: `container { image, agent_command, agent_args, network_allow }`\n- **Host workflows**: `host { agent_command, agent_args }`\n- **Step-level**: `prompt, run, workflow_name, max_attempts, timeout, agent_command, agent_args, feedback, prompt_step`\n\n**Results Declaration:**\n```go\nresults = [success, fail, retry]\n```\nDeclares possible outcomes this step can report.\n\n**Wiring with Output Mapping:**\n```\nstep_a:success -> step_b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output[0].name ]\n```\nExtracts values from step output as JSON and injects as environment variables.\n\n**Built-in Terminal Steps:**\n- `done` — successful completion\n- `abort` — failure with error\n\n**Execution Model:**\n- **Container workflows**: Parsed and executed by `cloche-agent` inside Docker. Agent walks the graph until reaching a terminal.\n- **Host workflows**: Parsed and executed by the daemon on the host machine. Three phases: `list-tasks` → `main` → `finalize`. Script steps run in the main git worktree (even if project is a linked worktree).\n\n---\n\n### 7. PATTERN FOR ADDING A NEW CLI SUBCOMMAND\n\n**Step-by-step implementation pattern:**\n\n**1. Add registration in main.go (lines 25-129):**\n```go\n// Add to the appropriate category:\n\n// For non-daemon commands (lines 40-77):\ncase \"mycommand\":\n    if hasHelpFlag(os.Args[2:]) {\n        printSubcommandHelp(\"mycommand\")\n        return\n    }\n    cmdMyCommand(os.Args[2:])\n    return\n\n// For daemon commands (lines 106-124):\ncase \"mycommand\":\n    cmdMyCommand(ctx, client, os.Args[2:])\n```\n\n**2. If daemon-required, add to daemonCmds map (lines 80-83):**\n```go\ndaemonCmds := map[string]bool{\n    \"run\": true, \"status\": true, /* ... */, \"mycommand\": true,\n}\n```\n\n**3. Add help text in help.go (subcommandHelp map, lines 10-305):**\n```go\n\"mycommand\": `cloche mycommand — One-line description\n\nLonger explanation of what the command does.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche mycommand [--flag <value>]\n\nFlags:\n  --flag <value>    Description\n\nExamples:\n  cloche mycommand\n`,\n```\n\n**4. Implement command function in appropriate file:**\n\nFor **non-daemon commands**:\n```go\nfunc cmdMyCommand(args []string) {\n    // Parse args\n    for i := 0; i < len(args); i++ {\n        switch args[i] {\n        case \"--flag\":\n            if i+1 < len(args) {\n                i++\n                // flag = args[i]\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    // Validation\n    // Logic\n    // Output\n}\n```\n\nFor **daemon-required commands**:\n```go\nfunc cmdMyCommand(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n    // Same pattern as above, but with access to gRPC client\n    // resp, err := client.SomeRPC(ctx, &pb.Request{...})\n}\n```\n\n**5. If adding new gRPC RPC, update proto file:**\n`/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n\nAdd service method and message types, regenerate with `protoc`.\n\n---\n\n### 8. KEY ARCHITECTURAL INSIGHTS\n\n**Hexagonal Architecture:**\n- Domain layer (`internal/domain`) is independent of infrastructure\n- Ports define interfaces (`internal/ports`)\n- Adapters implement ports (Docker, SQLite, gRPC, agents)\n- This enables testing and pluggable implementations\n\n**Workflow Execution Model:**\n- **Container**: One container per run. All steps execute inside. File state accumulates.\n- **Host**: Runs on host machine. Can orchestrate multiple container runs via `workflow_name` steps.\n\n**Task-Driven Orchestration:**\n- Host workflow has three phases (list-tasks, main, finalize)\n- Daemon picks first \"open\" task from JSONL output\n- Deduplication prevents rapid reassignment\n- Support for workflow evolution and self-improvement\n\n**Result-Based Flow Control:**\n- No explicit if/then—graph structure determines flow\n- Each step declares possible results\n- Wiring follows results\n- Enables dynamic rewiring without code changes\n\n**Output Mapping:**\n- Steps output JSON (or plain text)\n- Wiring can extract values via JSON path\n- Injected as environment variables into next step\n- Enables data flow through workflow\n\n---\n\n### 9. FILE LOCATIONS & ORGANIZATION\n\n**CLI Code:**\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` — Command dispatcher\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go` — Help system\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/init.go` — Project initialization\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/health.go` — Health query\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/poll.go` — Poll implementation\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/*.go` — One file per subcommand or functional group\n\n**Workflow DSL:**\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` — Parser (5 stages: lexer, recursive descent, inference, validation)\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/lexer.go` — Tokenization\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/token.go` — Token definitions\n\n**Domain:**\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` — Workflow, Step, Wire, OutputMapping types\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` — Run and StepExecution types\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/health.go` — Health aggregation\n\n**Ports & Interfaces:**\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` — RunStore, CaptureStore, LogStore, EvolutionStore\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go` — ContainerRuntime, ContainerConfig\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go` — AgentAdapter\n\n**Configuration Files:**\n- `/workspace/.cloche/develop.cloche` — Example container workflow\n- `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche` — Example host workflow (3 phases)\n- `/workspace/docs/workflows.md` — DSL documentation\n- `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md` — CLI reference\n\n---\n\n### 10. KEY DATA TYPES SUMMARY\n\n| Type | Location | Purpose |\n|------|----------|---------|\n| `Workflow` | domain/workflow.go | Entire workflow definition (name, steps, wiring, config) |\n| `Step` | domain/workflow.go | Single step (name, type, results, config) |\n| `StepType` | domain/workflow.go | Enum: agent, script, workflow |\n| `Wire` | domain/workflow.go | Directed edge (from:result→to, with optional output mapping) |\n| `OutputMapping` | domain/workflow.go | Maps step output to env var via JSON path |\n| `Run` | domain/run.go | Execution record (ID, state, container, step execs) |\n| `StepExecution` | domain/run.go | Single step execution (name, result, timestamps, logs) |\n| `RunState` | domain/run.go | Enum: pending, running, succeeded, failed, cancelled |\n| `Collect` | domain/workflow.go | Multi-step result aggregation (all/any mode) |\n\nThis comprehensive exploration provides a complete picture of how Cloche is structured, how workflows are defined and executed, and exactly how to extend the CLI with new subcommands following established patterns."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a5469156fb2965161 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 64503\ntool_uses: 27\nduration_ms: 70377</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"824f09ed-450b-4e33-88c5-1585f66e5eba","uuid":"7b0d9e1b-a66a-4bda-9fbc-7557a9996fe4","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore this Go project to understand:\n\n1. The CLI command structure in cmd/cloche/ - how subcommands are registered\n2. The workflow DSL types in internal/domain/ - Workflow, Step, Result types\n3. How workflows are parsed/loaded (look for workflow parsing code)\n4. The existing subcommand implementations (run, status, logs, stop) for patterns to follow\n5. The ports/ interfaces, especially anything related to workflow loading\n6. The docs/workflows.md for DSL syntax\n\nBe very thorough - read all relevant files completely. I need to understand the full pattern for adding a new CLI subcommand and the workflow data model.","agentId":"a5469156fb2965161","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me compile my findings into a detailed report.\n\n## Comprehensive Cloche Project Analysis\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the Cloche grow-coding system. Here's my detailed analysis covering all aspects you requested:\n\n---\n\n### 1. CLI COMMAND STRUCTURE (cmd/cloche/main.go)\n\n**Architecture Pattern:**\n- Cloche uses a **two-tier command handling system**:\n  1. **Commands without daemon connection** (lines 41-77): init, health, get, set, tasks\n  2. **Daemon-requiring commands** (lines 79-129): run, status, logs, poll, list, stop, delete, loop, shutdown\n\n**How Subcommands Are Registered:**\nEach subcommand is dispatched via a `switch` statement on `os.Args[1]`, then help is handled before execution:\n\n```go\nswitch os.Args[1] {\ncase \"init\":\n    if hasHelpFlag(os.Args[2:]) {\n        printSubcommandHelp(\"init\")\n        return\n    }\n    cmdInit(os.Args[2:])\n    return\ncase \"run\":\n    // ... connect to daemon first\n    cmdRun(ctx, client, os.Args[2:])\n}\n```\n\n**Help System:**\n- Help text is centralized in `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go` in the `subcommandHelp` map (lines 10-305)\n- Each subcommand entry includes usage, flags, examples, and detailed descriptions formatted for LLM consumption\n- Help is triggered via `--help`, `-h`, or `help <command>`\n\n**Subcommand Categories:**\n| Category | Commands | Notes |\n|----------|----------|-------|\n| Project Setup | init, health | No daemon needed |\n| Workflow Runs | run, status, logs, poll, list, stop, delete | Daemon-based gRPC calls |\n| Orchestration | tasks, loop | Uses gRPC or HTTP API |\n| Context | get, set | Run-specific state management |\n| Daemon Mgmt | shutdown | Direct gRPC |\n\n---\n\n### 2. WORKFLOW DSL TYPES (internal/domain/workflow.go)\n\n**Core Data Model:**\n\n```go\ntype Workflow struct {\n    Name      string                    // e.g. \"develop\"\n    Location  WorkflowLocation          // \"container\" or \"host\"\n    Steps     map[string]*Step          // Named steps\n    Wiring    []Wire                    // step:result -> step mappings\n    Collects  []Collect                 // Multi-result aggregation (fanout join)\n    EntryStep string                    // First step to execute\n    Config    map[string]string         // Workflow-level config (container.image, host.agent_command)\n}\n\ntype Step struct {\n    Name    string                      // Unique within workflow\n    Type    StepType                    // agent | script | workflow\n    Results []string                    // Declared possible outcomes\n    Config  map[string]string           // Step-specific config (prompt, run, workflow_name, etc)\n}\n\ntype Wire struct {\n    From      string                    // Source step\n    Result    string                    // Which result triggers this wire\n    To        string                    // Target step (\"done\" or \"abort\" for terminals)\n    OutputMap []OutputMapping           // Optional env var injection\n}\n\ntype OutputMapping struct {\n    EnvVar string                       // Env var to set (e.g. \"TASK_ID\")\n    Path   OutputPath                   // JSON path expression (e.g. output.id)\n}\n\ntype OutputPath struct {\n    Segments []PathSegment              // Navigates JSON: field access or array indexing\n}\n```\n\n**Step Type Inference (parser.go:224-253):**\nThe parser infers step type from the presence of fields:\n- `prompt` → `StepTypeAgent`\n- `run` → `StepTypeScript`\n- `workflow_name` → `StepTypeWorkflow` (host-only)\n\nA step **must have exactly one** of these three. Having zero or multiple is a parse error.\n\n**Results and Wiring:**\n- Each step declares its possible results (e.g., `results = [success, fail, retry]`)\n- Wiring connects results to next steps: `step_a:success -> step_b`\n- **Every declared result must be wired** (validation enforces this at parse time)\n- **All steps must be reachable** from the entry step\n- **Fanout** supported: multiple wires from the same (step, result) pair\n- **Collect mode** supports awaiting multiple step results before proceeding\n\n**Location-Based Validation:**\n```go\nfunc (w *Workflow) ValidateLocation() error {\n    if w.Location == LocationContainer {\n        // workflow_name steps forbidden in container workflows\n    }\n}\n```\n\nOnly host workflows (host.cloche) can dispatch container workflow runs via `workflow_name` steps.\n\n---\n\n### 3. WORKFLOW PARSING & LOADING\n\n**Parser Design (internal/dsl/parser.go):**\n\n```go\n// Single workflow parsing\nfunc Parse(input string, opts ...ParseOption) (*domain.Workflow, error)\nfunc ParseForContainer(input string) (*domain.Workflow, error)\nfunc ParseForHost(input string) (*domain.Workflow, error)\n\n// Multiple workflows in host.cloche\nfunc ParseAllForHost(input string) (map[string]*domain.Workflow, error)\n```\n\n**Lexer + Recursive Descent Parser:**\n- Lexer tokenizes input (tokens defined in `/workspace/internal/dsl/token.go`)\n- Tokens: `TokenIdent`, `TokenString`, `TokenLBrace`, `TokenRBrace`, `TokenArrow` (`->`), `TokenColon`, `TokenDot`, `TokenEquals`, `TokenLBracket`, `TokenRBracket`, `TokenComma`, `TokenInt`\n- Parser uses lookahead (current + peek tokens) for recursive descent\n- Comments and whitespace skipped by lexer\n\n**Parsing Phases:**\n\n1. **Workflow header** (line 99): `workflow \"<name>\" { ... }`\n2. **Config blocks** (line 164): `container { image = \"...\" }` or `host { agent_command = \"...\" }`\n3. **Steps** (line 197): `step <name> { ... }` with fields parsed recursively\n4. **Wiring** (line 402): `step_a:result -> step_b [ENVVAR = output.path, ...]`\n5. **Collect** (line 513): `collect all(step1:result, step2:result) -> target`\n\n**Output Path Parsing (line 478):**\nNavigates JSON structure: `output`, `output.field`, `output[0]`, `output.a.b.c`, `output.items[0].name`\n\n**Validation Sequence:**\n- Parse-time checks for duplicate workflows, missing names\n- `Workflow.ValidateLocation()` (line 233): ensures workflow_name only in host workflows\n- `Workflow.Validate()` (line 145): full DAG validation\n- `Workflow.ValidateConfig()` (line 261): warns about unrecognized config keys\n\n---\n\n### 4. EXISTING SUBCOMMAND IMPLEMENTATIONS\n\n**Pattern across all subcommands:**\n\n```go\nfunc cmd<Name>(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n    // 1. Parse flags/arguments\n    var workflow, prompt string\n    for i := 0; i < len(args); i++ {\n        switch args[i] {\n        case \"--workflow\":\n            workflow = args[i+1]\n            i++\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // 2. Validate required arguments\n    if workflow == \"\" {\n        fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: ...\\n\")\n        os.Exit(1)\n    }\n    \n    // 3. Call daemon via gRPC\n    resp, err := client.RunWorkflow(ctx, &pb.RunWorkflowRequest{...})\n    if err != nil {\n        fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n        os.Exit(1)\n    }\n    \n    // 4. Format and output result\n    fmt.Printf(\"Started run: %s\\n\", resp.RunId)\n}\n```\n\n**Key Implementations:**\n\n**cmdRun** (main.go:133-193):\n- Resolves workflow image from `.cloche/<name>.cloche` (dsl.ParseForContainer)\n- Sends RunWorkflowRequest to daemon\n- Prints run ID\n\n**cmdStatus** (main.go:195-232):\n- Queries GetStatus RPC\n- Formats tabular output with run state, steps, timestamps, error\n\n**cmdLogs** (main.go:290-375):\n- Handles `--step <name>`, `--type <full|script|llm>`, `--follow` flags\n- Uses gRPC metadata header for follow mode\n- Streams log entries, parses Claude Code streams\n\n**cmdPoll** (poll.go:12-77):\n- Polls GetStatus every 2 seconds\n- Tracks step count and state changes\n- Exits with status code 0 (succeeded) or 1 (failed/cancelled)\n- Detects container death after 1-minute threshold\n\n**cmdList** (main.go:234-288):\n- Optional `--all` flag to list all projects\n- Default filters to current project directory\n- Formats tabular output with truncated titles/errors\n\n**Non-daemon Commands:**\n\n**cmdInit** (init.go:138-232):\n- Creates `.cloche/` directory structure\n- Writes workflow templates, Dockerfile, prompt files\n- Updates .gitignore for run directories\n- Flags: `--workflow`, `--base-image`\n\n**cmdGet/cmdSet** (main.go:563-613):\n- Resolve run context from env vars: CLOCHE_RUN_ID, CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR\n- Read/write from run's context.json file\n- Set supports reading from stdin with `-` value\n\n**cmdHealth** (health.go:24-92):\n- Calls HTTP endpoint `/api/projects`\n- Formats project health with pass/fail counts\n- Color codes status (green/yellow/red) for TTY\n\n**cmdTasks** (main.go:450-534):\n- Calls HTTP endpoint `/api/projects/{projectDir}/tasks`\n- Parses JSON task list\n- Formats table with ID, status, assignment, run, title\n\n---\n\n### 5. PORTS/INTERFACES (internal/ports/)\n\n**RunStore Interface** (store.go:10-19):\n```go\ntype RunStore interface {\n    CreateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\n    GetRun(ctx context.Context, id string) (*domain.Run, error)\n    UpdateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\n    DeleteRun(ctx context.Context, id string) error\n    ListRuns(ctx context.Context, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListProjects(ctx context.Context) ([]string, error)\n    ListChildRuns(ctx context.Context, parentRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n}\n```\n\n**CaptureStore Interface** (store.go:21-24):\nPersists step execution logs and metadata (StepExecution records).\n\n**LogStore Interface** (store.go:36-41):\nManages log files by type (full, script, llm), indexed by run and step.\n\n**ContainerRuntime Interface** (container.go:24-33):\n```go\ntype ContainerRuntime interface {\n    Start(ctx context.Context, cfg ContainerConfig) (containerID string, err error)\n    Stop(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n    AttachOutput(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n    Wait(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (exitCode int, err error)\n    CopyFrom(ctx context.Context, containerID string, srcPath, dstPath string) error\n    Logs(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (string, error)\n    Remove(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n    Inspect(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (*ContainerStatus, error)\n}\n```\n\n**AgentAdapter Interface** (agent.go:10-12):\n```go\ntype AgentAdapter interface {\n    Name() string\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (result string, err error)\n}\n```\nAbstraction for any coding agent (Claude Code, Codex, etc).\n\n**EvolutionStore Interface** (store.go:54-58):\nTracks workflow mutations and self-evolution history.\n\n---\n\n### 6. WORKFLOW DSL SYNTAX (docs/workflows.md)\n\n**Complete Grammar:**\n\n```\nworkflow \"<name>\" {\n  [ <config-block> ]\n  [ <step-definitions> ]\n  [ <wiring> ]\n  [ <collect> ]\n}\n\n<config-block> ::= \"container\" | \"host\" \"{\" <key-value-pairs> \"}\"\n<key-value-pairs> ::= <ident> \"=\" <value> [ \",\" <key-value-pairs> ]\n\n<step-definitions> ::= \"step\" <ident> \"{\" <fields> \"}\"\n<fields> ::= <key> \"=\" <value> [ <fields> ]\n           | \"results\" \"=\" \"[\" <ident-list> \"]\" [ <fields> ]\n           | <key> \"{\" <fields> \"}\" [ <fields> ]\n\n<wiring> ::= <ident> \":\" <ident> \"->\" <ident> [ \"[\" <output-mappings> \"]\" ]\n<output-mappings> ::= <ident> \"=\" <path> [ \",\" <output-mappings> ]\n<path> ::= \"output\" [ \".\" <ident> ]* [ \"[\" <int> \"]\" ]*\n\n<collect> ::= \"collect\" (\"all\" | \"any\") \"(\" <conditions> \")\" \"->\" <ident>\n<conditions> ::= <ident> \":\" <ident> [ \",\" <conditions> ]\n```\n\n**Step Type Inference:**\n- `prompt` field → Agent step\n- `run` field → Script step\n- `workflow_name` field → Workflow dispatch (host-only)\n- Exactly one required\n\n**Config Keys:**\n- **Container workflows**: `container { image, agent_command, agent_args, network_allow }`\n- **Host workflows**: `host { agent_command, agent_args }`\n- **Step-level**: `prompt, run, workflow_name, max_attempts, timeout, agent_command, agent_args, feedback, prompt_step`\n\n**Results Declaration:**\n```go\nresults = [success, fail, retry]\n```\nDeclares possible outcomes this step can report.\n\n**Wiring with Output Mapping:**\n```\nstep_a:success -> step_b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output[0].name ]\n```\nExtracts values from step output as JSON and injects as environment variables.\n\n**Built-in Terminal Steps:**\n- `done` — successful completion\n- `abort` — failure with error\n\n**Execution Model:**\n- **Container workflows**: Parsed and executed by `cloche-agent` inside Docker. Agent walks the graph until reaching a terminal.\n- **Host workflows**: Parsed and executed by the daemon on the host machine. Three phases: `list-tasks` → `main` → `finalize`. Script steps run in the main git worktree (even if project is a linked worktree).\n\n---\n\n### 7. PATTERN FOR ADDING A NEW CLI SUBCOMMAND\n\n**Step-by-step implementation pattern:**\n\n**1. Add registration in main.go (lines 25-129):**\n```go\n// Add to the appropriate category:\n\n// For non-daemon commands (lines 40-77):\ncase \"mycommand\":\n    if hasHelpFlag(os.Args[2:]) {\n        printSubcommandHelp(\"mycommand\")\n        return\n    }\n    cmdMyCommand(os.Args[2:])\n    return\n\n// For daemon commands (lines 106-124):\ncase \"mycommand\":\n    cmdMyCommand(ctx, client, os.Args[2:])\n```\n\n**2. If daemon-required, add to daemonCmds map (lines 80-83):**\n```go\ndaemonCmds := map[string]bool{\n    \"run\": true, \"status\": true, /* ... */, \"mycommand\": true,\n}\n```\n\n**3. Add help text in help.go (subcommandHelp map, lines 10-305):**\n```go\n\"mycommand\": `cloche mycommand — One-line description\n\nLonger explanation of what the command does.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche mycommand [--flag <value>]\n\nFlags:\n  --flag <value>    Description\n\nExamples:\n  cloche mycommand\n`,\n```\n\n**4. Implement command function in appropriate file:**\n\nFor **non-daemon commands**:\n```go\nfunc cmdMyCommand(args []string) {\n    // Parse args\n    for i := 0; i < len(args); i++ {\n        switch args[i] {\n        case \"--flag\":\n            if i+1 < len(args) {\n                i++\n                // flag = args[i]\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    // Validation\n    // Logic\n    // Output\n}\n```\n\nFor **daemon-required commands**:\n```go\nfunc cmdMyCommand(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n    // Same pattern as above, but with access to gRPC client\n    // resp, err := client.SomeRPC(ctx, &pb.Request{...})\n}\n```\n\n**5. If adding new gRPC RPC, update proto file:**\n`/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n\nAdd service method and message types, regenerate with `protoc`.\n\n---\n\n### 8. KEY ARCHITECTURAL INSIGHTS\n\n**Hexagonal Architecture:**\n- Domain layer (`internal/domain`) is independent of infrastructure\n- Ports define interfaces (`internal/ports`)\n- Adapters implement ports (Docker, SQLite, gRPC, agents)\n- This enables testing and pluggable implementations\n\n**Workflow Execution Model:**\n- **Container**: One container per run. All steps execute inside. File state accumulates.\n- **Host**: Runs on host machine. Can orchestrate multiple container runs via `workflow_name` steps.\n\n**Task-Driven Orchestration:**\n- Host workflow has three phases (list-tasks, main, finalize)\n- Daemon picks first \"open\" task from JSONL output\n- Deduplication prevents rapid reassignment\n- Support for workflow evolution and self-improvement\n\n**Result-Based Flow Control:**\n- No explicit if/then—graph structure determines flow\n- Each step declares possible results\n- Wiring follows results\n- Enables dynamic rewiring without code changes\n\n**Output Mapping:**\n- Steps output JSON (or plain text)\n- Wiring can extract values via JSON path\n- Injected as environment variables into next step\n- Enables data flow through workflow\n\n---\n\n### 9. FILE LOCATIONS & ORGANIZATION\n\n**CLI Code:**\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` — Command dispatcher\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go` — Help system\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/init.go` — Project initialization\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/health.go` — Health query\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/poll.go` — Poll implementation\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/*.go` — One file per subcommand or functional group\n\n**Workflow DSL:**\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` — Parser (5 stages: lexer, recursive descent, inference, validation)\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/lexer.go` — Tokenization\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/token.go` — Token definitions\n\n**Domain:**\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` — Workflow, Step, Wire, OutputMapping types\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` — Run and StepExecution types\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/health.go` — Health aggregation\n\n**Ports & Interfaces:**\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` — RunStore, CaptureStore, LogStore, EvolutionStore\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go` — ContainerRuntime, ContainerConfig\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go` — AgentAdapter\n\n**Configuration Files:**\n- `/workspace/.cloche/develop.cloche` — Example container workflow\n- `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche` — Example host workflow (3 phases)\n- `/workspace/docs/workflows.md` — DSL documentation\n- `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md` — CLI reference\n\n---\n\n### 10. KEY DATA TYPES SUMMARY\n\n| Type | Location | Purpose |\n|------|----------|---------|\n| `Workflow` | domain/workflow.go | Entire workflow definition (name, steps, wiring, config) |\n| `Step` | domain/workflow.go | Single step (name, type, results, config) |\n| `StepType` | domain/workflow.go | Enum: agent, script, workflow |\n| `Wire` | domain/workflow.go | Directed edge (from:result→to, with optional output mapping) |\n| `OutputMapping` | domain/workflow.go | Maps step output to env var via JSON path |\n| `Run` | domain/run.go | Execution record (ID, state, container, step execs) |\n| `StepExecution` | domain/run.go | Single step execution (name, result, timestamps, logs) |\n| `RunState` | domain/run.go | Enum: pending, running, succeeded, failed, cancelled |\n| `Collect` | domain/workflow.go | Multi-step result aggregation (all/any mode) |\n\nThis comprehensive exploration provides a complete picture of how Cloche is structured, how workflows are defined and executed, and exactly how to extend the CLI with new subcommands following established patterns."}],"totalDurationMs":70377,"totalTokens":64503,"totalToolUseCount":27,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1038,"cache_read_input_tokens":58068,"output_tokens":5397,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1038},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
