{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_014ZpNLkdh2jYLWtEmgLBuVm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n**New file: `cmd/cloche/workflow.go`**\n- `cmdWorkflow` — parses `--project`/`-p` flag and optional workflow name arg\n- **List mode** (no args): discovers all `.cloche/*.cloche` files, parses them, groups by container/host type\n- **Graph mode** (`cloche workflow <name>`): loads the named workflow and renders an ASCII-art graph\n- `renderWorkflowGraph` — BFS-ordered step boxes with tree-style wiring below each step\n- Wire colorization: green for success, red for fail/failed, blue/yellow/orange/magenta cycling for other results; DONE colored green, ABORT colored red; TTY-aware\n- Wire merging: wires to the same destination are merged (e.g., `fail, give-up ──▶ ABORT`)\n- Consistent box widths across all steps in a workflow\n- Entry step marked with `◀ entry`\n\n**Modified files:**\n- `cmd/cloche/main.go` — registered `workflow` as a non-daemon command\n- `cmd/cloche/help.go` — added help text and top-level help entry under \"Workflow Info\"\n- `cmd/cloche/help_test.go` — added `\"workflow\"` to the subcommand help existence check\n\n**New file: `cmd/cloche/workflow_test.go`** — 17 tests covering BFS ordering, cycle handling, wire merging, color assignment, box width consistency, workflow discovery, loading from container/host files, the full develop workflow graph, and collect blocks.\n\nCLOCHE_RESULT:success"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":296,"cache_read_input_tokens":83063,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":296},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"824f09ed-450b-4e33-88c5-1585f66e5eba","uuid":"a965f7dd-2a17-4fdc-b698-88f0deeada9d"}
